\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {13}{\ignorespaces Year-1 sea ice and snow: implicit-solve run (blue) vs the movcav16-era state (orange) vs the 500-year-stable v3.4 reference (black dashed). Our runs track each other --- the crash fixes did not degrade climate --- but the reference collapses its SH ice almost completely each summer while ours retains $\sim $7k nodes, and its winter pack carries 0.03--0.08\,m of snow against our 0.2--0.3\,m. Bottom maps (same scale): December snow depth --- our thick band hugs the Antarctic coast; the reference is nearly bare.}}{20}{figure.13}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:seaiceref}{{13}{20}{Year-1 sea ice and snow: implicit-solve run (blue) vs the movcav16-era state (orange) vs the 500-year-stable v3.4 reference (black dashed). Our runs track each other --- the crash fixes did not degrade climate --- but the reference collapses its SH ice almost completely each summer while ours retains $\sim $7k nodes, and its winter pack carries 0.03--0.08\,m of snow against our 0.2--0.3\,m. Bottom maps (same scale): December snow depth --- our thick band hugs the Antarctic coast; the reference is nearly bare}{figure.13}{}}
