\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {14}{\ignorespaces The extent of the coastal pile-up in the (pre-fix) movcav runs: annual-max and December snow depth, and the seasonal cycle. The thick snow is a band hugging the ice-shelf front (eastern Weddell/Fimbul, Amundsen), bounded at 2--2.6\,m by an autumn melt-back. Later runs that lost this melt-back drifted monotonically to 3.5\,m --- the insulation that raised Bug IV's loop gain.}}{21}{figure.14}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:snowband}{{14}{21}{The extent of the coastal pile-up in the (pre-fix) movcav runs: annual-max and December snow depth, and the seasonal cycle. The thick snow is a band hugging the ice-shelf front (eastern Weddell/Fimbul, Amundsen), bounded at 2--2.6\,m by an autumn melt-back. Later runs that lost this melt-back drifted monotonically to 3.5\,m --- the insulation that raised Bug IV's loop gain}{figure.14}{}}
